abstract: The progress of Warren Vache, the jazz trumpeter, cornetist and flugelhornist, has been impressively consistent during the last decade. Starting out with Dixieland groups in New Jersey, he absorbed the swing era styles as one of Benny Goodman's frequent side men during the past few years, and, on his own, moved on to the post-swing influence of Clifford Brown.
